rules: Rule1: Provided that the chef has a job, the Food Expo is successful.
Rule2: Under the condition that Gourmet Co. wins the award for best display, the Food Expo is successful.
Rule3: Whenever Fine Foods Inc. wins the award for best display, the Food Expo is successful.
Rule4: Provided that Fine Foods Inc. is nominated for best display, Gourmet Co. wins the award for best display or Fine Foods Inc. wins the award for best display.
Rule5: If the Food Expo is on schedule, then it is not the case that the Food Expo is delayed.
Rule6: If the city council approves the permit, then, assuming that it is not the case that if the Food Expo is not successful then it is not funded by the city council, the Food Expo is on schedule.
Rule7: Either the city council approves the permit or the mayor approves the permit.

Rule8: Provided that the mayor approves the permit, then, under the condition that it is not the case that if the Food Expo is not successful then it is not funded by the city council, the Food Expo is on schedule.
Rule9: If the fire department conducts the safety check, then, provided that the Food Expo requires a safety check, the Food Expo is not extended.
Rule10: The fire department conducts the safety check or the health department conducts the safety check.
Rule11: Provided that the Food Expo passes the safety check, then, whenever the Food Expo requires a safety check, the Food Expo is not extended.

Rule12: Either the Food Expo is rescheduled, or, if it is not the case that if the health department conducts the safety check then the Food Expo passes the safety check, then the Food Expo fails the safety check.
Rule13: Gourmet Co. is invited to the keynote or Fine Foods Inc. is invited to the keynote.
Rule14: Under the condition that Fine Foods Inc. is invited to the keynote, then, if the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., Gourmet Co. presents a new product.
Rule15: Provided that Fine Foods Inc. declines the keynote, it is not the case that Gourmet Co. declines the keynote.
Rule16: If a reported violation is confirmed, then either a violation is reported to the fire department or, provided that the Food Expo exceeds capacity, the Food Expo violates code.

Rule17: If the chef attends the Food Expo, then, under the condition that it is not the case that if the chef does not have a job then the chef works in the north region, the chef works in the south region.
Rule18: The chef attends the Food Expo or the sous chef attends the Food Expo.

Rule19: Provided that the sous chef attends the Food Expo, then, assuming that it is not the case that if the chef does not have a job then the chef works in the north region, the chef works in the south region.
Rule20: Under the condition that the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., Gourmet Co. demonstrates a new product.
Rule21: Provided that the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., it is not the case that Gourmet Co. presents a new product.
Rule22: Either the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., or, if the Food Expo is not successful, then the Food Expo has the local farm as a sponsor.
Rule23: Whenever Gourmet Co. demonstrates a new product, Gourmet Co. presents a new product.

Rule24: Provided that it is not the case that if the health department conducts the safety check then the Food Expo passes the safety check, it is not the case that the Food Expo fails the safety check.

Rule25: If it is not the case that if Gourmet Co. is invited to the keynote then, provided that the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., Gourmet Co. presents a new product, then Gourmet Co. declines the keynote.

Rule26: Under the condition that it is not the case that if Gourmet Co. is invited to the keynote then, if the Food Expo has a booth for Gourmet Co., Gourmet Co. presents a new product, then Fine Foods Inc. declines the keynote.

Rule27: If it is not the case that if it is not the case that if Gourmet Co. is nominated for best display then Fine Foods Inc. is nominated for best display then Gourmet Co. is disqualified, then Fine Foods Inc. is disqualified.

Rule28: Under the condition that it is not the case that if it is not the case that if the Food Expo is not successful then it is not funded by the city council then the Food Expo is on schedule, the Food Expo exceeds capacity.
Rule29: If it is not the case that if the Food Expo is not successful then the Food Expo is overcrowded, then the Food Expo is extended.
Rule30: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the Food Expo is not successful then it is not funded by the city council, the Food Expo is delayed.
Rule31: Provided that the chef does not have a job, it is not the case that the chef works in the north region.
Rule32: Under the condition that the Food Expo is not successful, the Food Expo is funded by the city council.
facts: Fact1: Gourmet Co. is nominated for best display.
Fact2: The Food Expo requires a safety check.
Fact3: A reported violation is confirmed.
Fact4: It is not the case that Gourmet Co. is disqualified.
Fact5: It is not the case that Fine Foods Inc. is disqualified.
Fact6: The Food Expo is not overcrowded.
Fact7: It is not the case that the Food Expo is rescheduled.
Fact8: The chef does not work in the south region.
Fact9: The Food Expo does not violate code.
Fact10: A violation is not reported to the fire department.
Fact11: It is not the case that the Food Expo has the local farm as a sponsor.
